                                                                                                               L amp;T inks nuclear power deal
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                              
	Mumbai, Jan. 16: Larsen amp; Toubro (L amp;T) today joined hands with Westinghouse Electric Company (WEC), a Toshiba group company, to pursue nuclear power plant business in India.        
	Under a memorandum of understanding signed between the two firms, Westinghouse will focus on design, engineering and procurement of major components for nuclear power plants while L amp;T will be responsible for construction and fabrication of structural, piping and equipment modules.        
	L amp;T expects an order book of Rs 60,000-80,000 crore from nuclear power business by 2020.         
	The MoU with WEC is for modular nuclear reactors. In L amp;T, our focus will be on providing a one-stop-shop solution for nuclear power plants, M.V. Kotwal, L amp;Ts senior executive vice-president said.        
	Meena Mutyala, vice-president and business leader of Westinghouse, said after the US, China and India were the big markets.        
	The announcement of the MoU saw the L amp;T stock gaining 1.8 per cent on the Bombay Stock Exchange to end at Rs 717.60.                                                                                                                                        
